        <abstract>
            <p>Has found the skull of the horned cock.</p>
            <p>With regard to CD’s suggestion about the possibility of producing a pigeon breed with differently coloured sexes, WBT reports the results of crossing blue and silver dragons; the silver offspring are almost always hens.</p> 
<p>Would like the latest edition of the <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi>.</p>  
<p>Encloses notes on volume one [of <hi rend="italic">Descent</hi>].</p> 
            <p>Encloses a photograph showing the bleaching effect of the sun’s rays on dun feathers in pigeons.</p>
        </abstract>
